From Shishin Yamada Subject Re Selling of PowerBook s In article A Murray Altheim writes In article r aaaINNt d senator bedfellow MIT EDU Daniel Cameron Daly writes I have a PB that I might be selling soon to upgrade to a Duo before graduation, to take advantage of the educational discount To those who have recently bought or sold a PB , what kind of price did you get Info on any config of PB appreciated Thanks Cam Daly Cam, Several months ago I bought a PB with external floppy, AppleTalk Remote Access, a Kensington case and AC adapter with complete documentation and in almost new condition, used for US I considered it a very good buy and am very cosy with my little baby now Murray Put me down for a PB with ext floppy, AppleTalk Remote Acces, AC adapter, and fresh out of box was used, but buyer switched to on arrival and sold unopened box Purchased last October for Later I bought a used PowerPort V bps internal fax modem for something like , I'm using right now Works great No real complaints I love my portable system got a color home setup also Mac II Reasoning was that MATLAB programs at school and other simulations of dynamic control systems sometimes took hours or overnight to run, tying up my Mac II I got the PB with fast modem to do light work and on the run stuff I figured I'd give it to my little sister next year when she goes to college It's running System now without any problems Also I sometimes do DEC terminal emulations with MATLAB on our university's VAX VMS nice thing that it benchmarks itself as an average of times faster than a mac IIfx So, the PB just does graphical output and terminal emulation not too hard at all for it It was a FABULOUS setup Weeee By the Way, all MATLAB software was on class accounts I was also the TA for a class that used SIMULAB SIMULINK We had site license and take home, then destroy later site release licenses No pirating there, incase you're wondering Great Program Just like to add, whatever future system you get, you can almost never get enuff memory Buy it while it's cheap that is buy it when you get the computer since it's usually cheaper than upgrading I ALWAYS run out of disk space But I have a syquest on the Mac IIsi, so I never worried about space before Got several carts shishin squish yamada